This paper deals with the security and resilience of infrastructure networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also presents a game-theoretic framework for analyzing the dynamics of infrastructure protection and recovery, which falls under the category of game theory and decision science (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of UAV-enabled communication networks for disaster recovery, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the optimization of utilities and costs, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the design and analysis of networked systems, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
